LXB - Linux X/Motif Builder Version 0.61
File: README 

01/14/18
BEP

Notes about the data directory:
	
	That directory was the way I settled on to define the actual
	size of data types in the XWindow System 20 years ago. Now
	I don't know. It aquires the sizes of various X datatypes
	and writes header files, and copies them into the include
	directory for use by the lxb source. The current *.h files
	in the include directory are for the Ubuntu v16 ported to a
	64-bit system.

01/14/18
	To compile the lxb program source under v16 of Ubuntu Linux
	on a 64-bit machine just:
		1) cd into the source directory
		2) type make, or make all

	To run lxb just type "lxb". Make sure your PATH is set to 
	search the current directory, or

		type: "./lxb"

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Below is old---


1) Building lxb

Unzip and untar the archive lxb-0.51.tar.gz. You will see several directories
and files.

In the "src" directory you can try the Makefile but most likely will have
to edit it.

Then:

make clean; make depend; make

2) Installing lxb

Their is an app-defaults file (Lxb-ad) in the "src" directory. However,
with this release it is not needed, and my advice is not to mess with
the resources unless you have to.

Install the executable somewhere your "path" refers to.

3) Using lxb

Limited documentation is in the file INSTRUCT. (TBD)

